                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>\n                                        <date>April 29. 1853</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Friend</p>\n                              <p>I have recd your Letter &amp; also that Book<lb/> treating upon the\n                                                  <date>sabbath</date> question, for which I<lb/>\n                                        return you my thanks.</p>\n                              <p>I have had no Time yet to collect that money<lb/> nor attending to\n                                        any of your other affairs; I have been of late so very busy\n                                        in receiving<lb/> Good &amp;c. I wish to tell you about the\n                                                  <add>Hebrew</add>,<lb/> which has been kept in a\n                                        very creditable<lb/> manner in general. The Synagogues\n                                        have<lb/> been extremely well attended, &amp; everything\n                                        carried<lb/> on in an orderly &amp; fine manner. We\n                                        have<lb/> at least now about 50 Jewish Families<lb/> &amp;\n                                        there are but very few exceptions which<lb/> did not have\n                                        “Mazos” As much as I can<lb/> learn, even those which don't\n                                        live <add>Hebrew</add> in general<lb/> have however had\n                                        “Mazos”. You may well<lb/> judge that Mazos have been in\n                                        Demand, from<lb/> the Fact, that they have been sold\n                                        from<lb/> 40 to 50 cts pr. pound; when the baking at<lb/>\n                                        first had been commenced they were sold<lb/> at 40 cts,\n                                        &amp; shortly after that they were raised<lb/> to 45 and 50\n                                        cts. pr. pound; You may perhaps</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3cj8861f/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
